  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: When user A on Ropsten during syncing receives funds request from user B on Ropsten with Upstream RPC (no sync) requested amount and text are not displayed in the message \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nRequested amount is shown on user A screen\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nRequested amount and text are not shown on user A screen - only icon of request is shown\r\n![2018-01-04 19 33 14](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/29711298/34576560-ebfb3d42-f186-11e7-9066-09b4e05483f6.jpg)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nAs user A:\r\n\r\n1. Open Status app\r\n2. Add user B as a contact\r\n3. Open Profile\r\n4. Click Network Settings\r\n5. Choose Ropsten network\r\n6. Click Connect\r\n7. Confirm and reopen the app\r\n8. Login again as user A\r\n9. Open 1-1 chat with user B. Syncing should start\r\n\r\nAs user B:\r\n\r\n1. Open Status app\r\n2. Open 1-1 chat with user A\r\n3. Add user A as a contact\r\n4. Click /request\r\n5. Input 0.01 amount after /request \r\n6. Click Send button\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\nStatus version: 0.9.12+\r\nOperating System user A: Real device OnePlus A5000, Android 7.1.1\r\nOperating System user B: Emulator Google Nexus 5, Android 6.0.0",
